/*! @page ControlCodes Embedding control codes into controls

Lightwave allows for controls codes to be used within most controls. Examples of these would be a checkmark or various arrows, which are used as icons.

They also allow the adjustement of the alignment of colour.

None of these are official and may change at any time.

They are escaped by a prefaced "\03" in a string.

An example would be "\03(i:MIMG_CHECKMARK)" which displays a checkmark.

# Control Codes
## (i:***)
embeds an image
Valid strings for *** are:
- MIMG_NONE
- MIMG_UPARROW
- MIMG_DOWNARROW
- MIMG_UPDARROW
- MIMG_CHECKMARK
- MIMG_LEFTRIGHT
- MIMG_LEFTARROW
- MIMG_RIGHTARROW
- MIMG_4ARROWS
- MIMG_CIRC_PLUS
- MIMG_CIRC_MINUS
- MIMG_CIRCLE
- MIMG_TREERIGHT
- MIMG_TREERIGHTO
- MIMG_TREEDOWN
- MIMG_TREEDOWNO
- MIMG_MENU
- MIMG_BULLET1
- MIMG_PAN
- MIMG_ROTATE
- MIMG_ZOOM
- MIMG_POPUPARROW
- MIMG_POPOUTARROW
- MIMG_VPEXPAND
- MIMG_VPCOLLAPSE
- MIMG_FLYOUT

## (g:KBSHORT_GAP)
inserts a short gap for a keyboard shortcut

## (j:*)
Justifies the following text, * may be:
- 2 justifies to the right

*/